## Description {#details}

This file implements a coalescing interval map for small objects.

KeyT objects are mapped to ValT objects. Intervals of keys that map to the same value are represented in a compressed form.

Iterators provide ordered access to the compressed intervals rather than the individual keys, and insert and erase operations use key intervals as well.

Like SmallVector, IntervalMap will store the first N intervals in the map object itself without any allocations. When space is exhausted it switches to a B+-tree representation with very small overhead for small key and value objects.

A Traits class specifies how keys are compared. It also allows IntervalMap to work with both closed and half-open intervals.

Keys and values are not stored next to each other in a std::pair, so we don&#39;t provide such a value&#95;type. Dereferencing iterators only returns the mapped value. The interval bounds are accessible through the start() and stop() iterator methods.

IntervalMap is optimized for small key and value objects, 4 or 8 bytes each is the optimal size. For large objects use std::map instead.

<Link id="l00125" /><CodeLine lineNumber="125"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00126" /><CodeLine lineNumber="126"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The IntervalMapInfo traits class is used to determine if a key is contained</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00127" /><CodeLine lineNumber="127"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// in an interval, and if two intervals are adjacent so they can be coalesced.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00128" /><CodeLine lineNumber="128"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The provided implementation works for closed integer intervals, other keys</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00129" /><CodeLine lineNumber="129"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// probably need a specialized version.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00130" /><CodeLine lineNumber="130"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00131" /><CodeLine lineNumber="131"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The point x is contained in &#91;a;b&#93; when !startLess(x, a) &amp;&amp; !stopLess(b, x).</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00132" /><CodeLine lineNumber="132"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00133" /><CodeLine lineNumber="133"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// It is assumed that (a;b&#93; half-open intervals are not used, only &#91;a;b) is</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00134" /><CodeLine lineNumber="134"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// allowed. This is so that stopLess(a, b) can be used to determine if two</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00135" /><CodeLine lineNumber="135"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// intervals overlap.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00136" /><CodeLine lineNumber="136"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00195" /><CodeLine lineNumber="195"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00196" /><CodeLine lineNumber="196"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//---                    IntervalMapImpl::NodeBase                         ---//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00197" /><CodeLine lineNumber="197"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00198" /><CodeLine lineNumber="198"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00199" /><CodeLine lineNumber="199"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Both leaf and branch nodes store vectors of pairs.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00200" /><CodeLine lineNumber="200"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Leaves store ((KeyT, KeyT), ValT) pairs, branches use (NodeRef, KeyT).</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00201" /><CodeLine lineNumber="201"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00202" /><CodeLine lineNumber="202"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Keys and values are stored in separate arrays to avoid padding caused by</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00203" /><CodeLine lineNumber="203"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// different object alignments. This also helps improve locality of reference</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00204" /><CodeLine lineNumber="204"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// when searching the keys.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00205" /><CodeLine lineNumber="205"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00206" /><CodeLine lineNumber="206"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The nodes don&#39;t know how many elements they contain - that information is</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00207" /><CodeLine lineNumber="207"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// stored elsewhere. Omitting the size field prevents padding and allows a node</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00208" /><CodeLine lineNumber="208"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// to fill the allocated cache lines completely.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00209" /><CodeLine lineNumber="209"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00210" /><CodeLine lineNumber="210"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// These are typical key and value sizes, the node branching factor (N), and</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00211" /><CodeLine lineNumber="211"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// wasted space when nodes are sized to fit in three cache lines (192 bytes):</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00212" /><CodeLine lineNumber="212"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00213" /><CodeLine lineNumber="213"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   T1  T2   N Waste  Used by</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00214" /><CodeLine lineNumber="214"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    4   4  24   0    Branch&lt;4&gt; (32-bit pointers)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00215" /><CodeLine lineNumber="215"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    8   4  16   0    Leaf&lt;4,4&gt;, Branch&lt;4&gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00216" /><CodeLine lineNumber="216"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    8   8  12   0    Leaf&lt;4,8&gt;, Branch&lt;8&gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00217" /><CodeLine lineNumber="217"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   16   4   9  12    Leaf&lt;8,4&gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00218" /><CodeLine lineNumber="218"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   16   8   8   0    Leaf&lt;8,8&gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00219" /><CodeLine lineNumber="219"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00220" /><CodeLine lineNumber="220"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00221" /><CodeLine lineNumber="221"></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00381" /><CodeLine lineNumber="381"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// IntervalMapImpl::distribute - Compute a new distribution of node elements</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00382" /><CodeLine lineNumber="382"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// after an overflow or underflow. Reserve space for a new element at Position,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00383" /><CodeLine lineNumber="383"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// and compute the node that will hold Position after redistributing node</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00384" /><CodeLine lineNumber="384"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// elements.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00385" /><CodeLine lineNumber="385"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00386" /><CodeLine lineNumber="386"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// It is required that</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00387" /><CodeLine lineNumber="387"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00388" /><CodeLine lineNumber="388"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   Elements == sum(CurSize), and</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00389" /><CodeLine lineNumber="389"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   Elements + Grow &lt;= Nodes &#42; Capacity.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00390" /><CodeLine lineNumber="390"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00391" /><CodeLine lineNumber="391"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// NewSize&#91;&#93; will be filled in such that:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00392" /><CodeLine lineNumber="392"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00393" /><CodeLine lineNumber="393"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   sum(NewSize) == Elements, and</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00394" /><CodeLine lineNumber="394"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   NewSize&#91;i&#93; &lt;= Capacity.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00395" /><CodeLine lineNumber="395"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00396" /><CodeLine lineNumber="396"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// The returned index is the node where Position will go, so:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00397" /><CodeLine lineNumber="397"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00398" /><CodeLine lineNumber="398"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   sum(NewSize&#91;0..idx-1&#93;) &lt;= Position</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00399" /><CodeLine lineNumber="399"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   sum(NewSize&#91;0..idx&#93;)   &gt;= Position</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00400" /><CodeLine lineNumber="400"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00401" /><CodeLine lineNumber="401"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// The last equality, sum(NewSize&#91;0..idx&#93;) == Position, can only happen when</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00402" /><CodeLine lineNumber="402"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Grow is set and NewSize&#91;idx&#93; == Capacity-1. The index points to the node</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00403" /><CodeLine lineNumber="403"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// before the one holding the Position&#39;th element where there is room for an</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00404" /><CodeLine lineNumber="404"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// insertion.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00405" /><CodeLine lineNumber="405"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00406" /><CodeLine lineNumber="406"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// @param Nodes    The number of nodes.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00407" /><CodeLine lineNumber="407"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// @param Elements Total elements in all nodes.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00408" /><CodeLine lineNumber="408"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// @param Capacity The capacity of each node.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00409" /><CodeLine lineNumber="409"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// @param CurSize  Array&#91;Nodes&#93; of current node sizes, or NULL.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00410" /><CodeLine lineNumber="410"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// @param NewSize  Array&#91;Nodes&#93; to receive the new node sizes.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00411" /><CodeLine lineNumber="411"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// @param Position Insert position.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00412" /><CodeLine lineNumber="412"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// @param Grow     Reserve space for a new element at Position.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00413" /><CodeLine lineNumber="413"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// @return         (node, offset) for Position.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00414" /><CodeLine lineNumber="414"><span class="doxyHighlight"><a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/intervalmapimpl/#ab92974e292699af764f4bd02d1f44448">IdxPair</a> <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/intervalmapimpl/#adc507d70d9385ae35dcdb70dc1bebc19">distribute</a>(</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">unsigned</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> Nodes, </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">unsigned</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> Elements, </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">unsigned</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> Capacity,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00415" /><CodeLine lineNumber="415"><span class="doxyHighlight">                   </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">const</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">unsigned</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> &#42;CurSize, </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">unsigned</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> NewSize&#91;&#93;,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00416" /><CodeLine lineNumber="416"><span class="doxyHighlight">                   </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">unsigned</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> Position, </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">bool</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> Grow);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00417" /><CodeLine lineNumber="417"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00418" /><CodeLine lineNumber="418"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00419" /><CodeLine lineNumber="419"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//---                   IntervalMapImpl::NodeSizer                         ---//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00420" /><CodeLine lineNumber="420"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00421" /><CodeLine lineNumber="421"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00422" /><CodeLine lineNumber="422"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Compute node sizes from key and value types.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00423" /><CodeLine lineNumber="423"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00424" /><CodeLine lineNumber="424"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The branching factors are chosen to make nodes fit in three cache lines.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00425" /><CodeLine lineNumber="425"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// This may not be possible if keys or values are very large. Such large objects</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00426" /><CodeLine lineNumber="426"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// are handled correctly, but a std::map would probably give better performance.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00427" /><CodeLine lineNumber="427"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00428" /><CodeLine lineNumber="428"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00429" /><CodeLine lineNumber="429"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00430" /><CodeLine lineNumber="430"><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">enum</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00431" /><CodeLine lineNumber="431"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Cache line size. Most architectures have 32 or 64 byte cache lines.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00432" /><CodeLine lineNumber="432"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// We use 64 bytes here because it provides good branching factors.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00433" /><CodeLine lineNumber="433" lineLink="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/intervalmapimpl/#aacf91952cde5989ab8c6b38b501021c1a4b980c1f20e48e79647774737cf4f1ce"><span class="doxyHighlight">  <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/intervalmapimpl/#aacf91952cde5989ab8c6b38b501021c1a4b980c1f20e48e79647774737cf4f1ce">Log2CacheLine</a> = 6,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00434" /><CodeLine lineNumber="434" lineLink="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/intervalmapimpl/#aacf91952cde5989ab8c6b38b501021c1a22be8a9f335245b5ce05d2a3d35a9221"><span class="doxyHighlight">  <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/intervalmapimpl/#aacf91952cde5989ab8c6b38b501021c1a22be8a9f335245b5ce05d2a3d35a9221">CacheLineBytes</a> = 1 &lt;&lt; <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/intervalmapimpl/#aacf91952cde5989ab8c6b38b501021c1a4b980c1f20e48e79647774737cf4f1ce">Log2CacheLine</a>,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00435" /><CodeLine lineNumber="435" lineLink="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/intervalmapimpl/#aacf91952cde5989ab8c6b38b501021c1ab4675b39ebff7a48b8f66be1e97f1575"><span class="doxyHighlight">  <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/intervalmapimpl/#aacf91952cde5989ab8c6b38b501021c1ab4675b39ebff7a48b8f66be1e97f1575">DesiredNodeBytes</a> = 3 &#42; <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/intervalmapimpl/#aacf91952cde5989ab8c6b38b501021c1a22be8a9f335245b5ce05d2a3d35a9221">CacheLineBytes</a></span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00471" /><CodeLine lineNumber="471"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00472" /><CodeLine lineNumber="472"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00473" /><CodeLine lineNumber="473"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//---                     IntervalMapImpl::NodeRef                         ---//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00474" /><CodeLine lineNumber="474"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00475" /><CodeLine lineNumber="475"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00476" /><CodeLine lineNumber="476"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// B+-tree nodes can be leaves or branches, so we need a polymorphic node</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00477" /><CodeLine lineNumber="477"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// pointer that can point to both kinds.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00478" /><CodeLine lineNumber="478"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00479" /><CodeLine lineNumber="479"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// All nodes are cache line aligned and the low 6 bits of a node pointer are</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00480" /><CodeLine lineNumber="480"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// always 0 These bits are used to store the number of elements in the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00481" /><CodeLine lineNumber="481"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// referenced node. Besides saving space, placing node sizes in the parents</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00482" /><CodeLine lineNumber="482"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// allow tree balancing algorithms to run without faulting cache lines for nodes</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00483" /><CodeLine lineNumber="483"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// that may not need to be modified.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00484" /><CodeLine lineNumber="484"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00485" /><CodeLine lineNumber="485"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// A NodeRef doesn&#39;t know whether it references a leaf node or a branch node.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00486" /><CodeLine lineNumber="486"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// It is the responsibility of the caller to use the correct types.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00487" /><CodeLine lineNumber="487"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00488" /><CodeLine lineNumber="488"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Nodes are never supposed to be empty, and it is invalid to store a node size</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00489" /><CodeLine lineNumber="489"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// of 0 in a NodeRef. The valid range of sizes is 1-64.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00490" /><CodeLine lineNumber="490"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00491" /><CodeLine lineNumber="491"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00492" /><CodeLine lineNumber="492"></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00545" /><CodeLine lineNumber="545"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00546" /><CodeLine lineNumber="546"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//---                      IntervalMapImpl::LeafNode                       ---//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00547" /><CodeLine lineNumber="547"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00548" /><CodeLine lineNumber="548"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00549" /><CodeLine lineNumber="549"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Leaf nodes store up to N disjoint intervals with corresponding values.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00550" /><CodeLine lineNumber="550"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00551" /><CodeLine lineNumber="551"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The intervals are kept sorted and fully coalesced so there are no adjacent</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00552" /><CodeLine lineNumber="552"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// intervals mapping to the same value.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00553" /><CodeLine lineNumber="553"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00554" /><CodeLine lineNumber="554"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// These constraints are always satisfied:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00555" /><CodeLine lineNumber="555"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00556" /><CodeLine lineNumber="556"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// - Traits::stopLess(start(i), stop(i))    - Non-empty, sane intervals.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00557" /><CodeLine lineNumber="557"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00558" /><CodeLine lineNumber="558"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// - Traits::stopLess(stop(i), start(i + 1) - Sorted.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00559" /><CodeLine lineNumber="559"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00560" /><CodeLine lineNumber="560"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// - value(i) != value(i + 1) || !Traits::adjacent(stop(i), start(i + 1))</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00561" /><CodeLine lineNumber="561"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//                                          - Fully coalesced.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00562" /><CodeLine lineNumber="562"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00563" /><CodeLine lineNumber="563"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00564" /><CodeLine lineNumber="564"></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00619" /><CodeLine lineNumber="619"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// insertFrom - Add mapping of &#91;a;b&#93; to y if possible, coalescing as much as</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00620" /><CodeLine lineNumber="620"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// possible. This may cause the node to grow by 1, or it may cause the node</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00621" /><CodeLine lineNumber="621"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// to shrink because of coalescing.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00622" /><CodeLine lineNumber="622"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// @param Pos  Starting index = insertFrom(0, size, a)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00623" /><CodeLine lineNumber="623"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// @param Size Number of elements in node.</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00626" /><CodeLine lineNumber="626"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// @param y    Value be mapped.</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00684" /><CodeLine lineNumber="684"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//---                   IntervalMapImpl::BranchNode                        ---//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00685" /><CodeLine lineNumber="685"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00686" /><CodeLine lineNumber="686"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00687" /><CodeLine lineNumber="687"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// A branch node stores references to 1--N subtrees all of the same height.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00688" /><CodeLine lineNumber="688"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00689" /><CodeLine lineNumber="689"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The key array in a branch node holds the rightmost stop key of each subtree.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00690" /><CodeLine lineNumber="690"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// It is redundant to store the last stop key since it can be found in the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00691" /><CodeLine lineNumber="691"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// parent node, but doing so makes tree balancing a lot simpler.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00692" /><CodeLine lineNumber="692"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00693" /><CodeLine lineNumber="693"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// It is unusual for a branch node to only have one subtree, but it can happen</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00694" /><CodeLine lineNumber="694"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// in the root node if it is smaller than the normal nodes.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00695" /><CodeLine lineNumber="695"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00696" /><CodeLine lineNumber="696"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// When all of the leaf nodes from all the subtrees are concatenated, they must</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00697" /><CodeLine lineNumber="697"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// satisfy the same constraints as a single leaf node. They must be sorted,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00698" /><CodeLine lineNumber="698"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// sane, and fully coalesced.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00699" /><CodeLine lineNumber="699"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00700" /><CodeLine lineNumber="700"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00711" /><CodeLine lineNumber="711"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// findFrom - Find the first subtree after i that may contain x.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00712" /><CodeLine lineNumber="712"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// @param i    Starting index for the search.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00713" /><CodeLine lineNumber="713"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// @param Size Number of elements in node.</span></CodeLine>
